abstract= {{In the context of vibrational spectroscopy in liquids, non-Condon effects refer to the dependence of
the vibrational transition dipole moment of a particular molecule on the rotational and translational
coordinates of all the molecules in the liquid. For strongly hydrogen-bonded systems, such as liquid
